<div class='communityQuestion'>
<div class='questionText'>
<a href="/questions/1054969-is-it-magical-realism-or-does-it-have">Is it magical realism, or does it have more of a Narnia vibe?</a>
</div>
<div class='communityQAFooter questionFooter'>
<ul class='questionFooterActions'>
<li class='footerItem like'>
<span class='likeItContainer' id='like_container_community_question_1054969'><a rel="nofollow" class="jsLike like_it" href="https://www.goodreads.com/user/new?remember=true&amp;return_url=%2Fbook%2Fshow%2F694997.The_Weirdstone_of_Brisingamen">like</a></span>

</li>
<li class='footerItem communityQuestionTimestamp'>
<a href="/questions/1054969-is-it-magical-realism-or-does-it-have">4 years ago</a>
</li>
<li class='footerItem communityQuestionPermalink'>
<a href="/questions/1054969-is-it-magical-realism-or-does-it-have">See all 2 answers</a>
</li>
</ul>
</div>

</div>
<div class='allCommunityAnswers'>
<div class='communityAnswer'>
<div class='communityAnswerBody'>
<div class='answererUserIcon'>
<a class="leftAlignedImage userPhoto" href="/user/show/143919781-alyss-broderick"><img alt="" src="https://s.gr-assets.com/images/nophoto/user/c_111x148.png" /></a>
</div>
<div class='communityAnswerTextContainer'>
<span class='communityAnswererName'>
<a href="/user/show/143919781-alyss-broderick">Alyss Broderick</a>
</span>
<span class='communityAnswerText'>
<span class="expandableContainer"><span class="truncatedContent">Super Narnia vibes. The magic world and the not magic world overlap more than in Narnia, but it&apos;s a very similar genre of kids needing to use their wi<a class="jsShow showAction" href="#">…more</a></span><span class="fullContent">Super Narnia vibes. The magic world and the not magic world overlap more than in Narnia, but it's a very similar genre of kids needing to use their wiles and courage to save the world from magical evil. As someone who's read lots of fantasy, it feels tropey and overdone... but like Dune, it feels that way because it invented the tropes :)<a class="jsHide hideAction" href="#">(less)</a></span></span>
</span>
</div>
</div>
