<div id="review_1775254987" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/1775254987" />
    <a title="Rosemary Atwell" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/15847499-rosemary-atwell"><img alt="Rosemary Atwell" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1356696365p2/15847499.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/1775254987?book_show_action=true">Nov 03, 2020</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Rosemary Atwell" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Rosemary Atwell" href="/user/show/15847499-rosemary-atwell">Rosemary Atwell</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1775254987" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer12041589811536773572">I always meant to read ‘The Owl Service’ and never did, so finding it alongside three other classic Garner tales in one slipcase means that I can finally add Mr. G to my long list of brilliant authors for grown up children.<br/><br/>Sense of place, atmosphere and pace are so beautifully and compellingly developed throughout that it’s hard not to devour ‘The Weirdstone of Brisingamen’ in one sitting. At sixty years young, an outstanding achievement.<br/></span>

          </span>
        </div>


